Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Thinly slice the @chestnut mushrooms{150%g} and @portobello mushrooms{2}. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(finely chopped, stalks and all). Pour half the the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} into a #bowl{}, add the @olive oil{1%tbsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix together and leave to the side.

When boiling, add the @penne pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. When the pasta is cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan. Drizzle with a little oil and stir through to stop it sticking together. Set aside off the heat.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the mushrooms and cook until browned, stirring occasionally, ~{6-7%minutes}. Once browned, reduce the heat to medium-low and add the onion. Cook, stirring frequently until the onion is nice and soft, ~{5-6%minutes}. Add the garlic and season with salt and pepper. Stir and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add the remaining @balsamic vinegar{}, stir and cook until evaporated, ~{1%minute}.

Pour the @water{150%ml} for the sauce into your frying pan and stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}. Increase the heat and bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer until reduced, ~{5-6%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Stir in the @creme fraiche{99%g} until well combined, bring back to the boil and add a good grind of @ground black pepper{}. Remove from the heat.

Add the drained pasta to the sauce along with three quarters of the @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated) and three quarters of the parsley. Stir everything together. Taste and add more salt and pepper if needed.

Spoon your pasta into #bowls{} and sprinkle the remaining cheese and parsley on top. Add the @wild rocket{40%g} to the balsamic dressing and toss together. Serve on top of the pasta and finish with a good grind of black pepper. Enjoy!

> MOD: If you've opted to get bacon lardons added to your meal, add the @?British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} to the pan before the mushrooms and cook for ~{2%minutes}. Then add the mushrooms and continue.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat. Cook lardons thoroughly.